summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on the United Nations Mission of Observers in Prevlaka (UNMOP), 
Having considered the Secretary-General's report of 2 January 2002,
Reaffirming Croatia's sovereignty and territorial integrity,
Noting the Joint Declaration of 30 September 1992, and the Agreement on Normalization of Relations of 23 August 1996,
1. Authorizes UNMOP to continue monitoring the demilitarization of the Prevlaka peninsula until 15 July 2002;
2. Calls on parties to cease violations of the demilitarized regime and ensure observers' safety and freedom of movement;
3. Welcomes progress in normalization of relations and establishment of an interstate Border Commission, urging parties to accelerate efforts towards a negotiated settlement;
4. Encourages parties to consider confidence-building measures;
5. Requests parties to report bimonthly on bilateral negotiations and Border Commission progress;
6. Requests UNMOP and the multinational stabilization force to cooperate fully;
7. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
